  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      It seems that the aldehydes and NO2, at the levels found indoor, could be the aggravating
      factors for an allergic response. However this effect has not been demonstrated. The
      investigators plan to study the effect of exposure to standard doses of these pollutants on
      the bronchial reactivity as measured by bronchial challenge tests with dust mite extract in
      volunteers asthmatic, allergic to house dust mite.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
